.TH LPF-FMT 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.1.2" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-fmt \- format policy files deterministically
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf fmt [\-\-check] [\-\-json] <policy>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Format policy files deterministically for review and CI.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-check
fail when formatting would change the policy
.TP
\-\-json
emit machine\-readable formatted text or diagnostics
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf fmt /etc/lpf.conf
lpf fmt \-\-check /etc/lpf.conf
lpf fmt \-\-json fixtures/policies/basic.lpf
.SH FILES
/etc/lpf.conf
.SH SAFETY NOTES
Formatting must not change policy semantics.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-check(8), lpf.conf(5)
